!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

boy /bɔɪ/

(boys) 

1. N-COUNT A boy is a child who will grow up to be a man. 男孩 

例： He was still just a boy. 他还只是个男孩。 

2. N-COUNT You can refer to a young man as a boy , especially when talking about relationships between boys and girls. 小伙子 

例： ...the age when girls get interested in boys. …女孩儿开始对小伙子感兴趣的年纪。 

3. N-COUNT Someone's boy is their son. 儿子 [非正式] 

例： Eric was my cousin Edward's boy. 埃里克是我堂兄爱德华的儿子。 

4. N-COUNT You can refer to a man as a boy , especially when you are talking about him in an affectionate way. 小伙儿 [非正式] 

例： ...the local boy who made president. …那个当上总统的本地小伙儿。 

5. INTERJ Some people say ' boy ' or ' oh boy ' in order to express feelings of excitement or admiration. 好家伙 (表示兴奋或羡慕) [美国英语] [非正式] 

例： Oh boy! what resourceful children I have. 好家伙！我的孩子们多机智啊。

